comments: Grant (POR) establishes himself in Nembhard's (IND) path and avoids delivering contact when setting the pick.
Nesmith (IND) moves alongside Simons' (POR) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Lillard (POR) extends his arm towards the ball and some contact occurs with the ball and Hield's (IND) hand that is on the ball, which Hield is able to play on through.
Turner (IND) moves alongside Lillard's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs after the pick is set.
Nurkic (POR) establishes himself in Nembhard's (IND) path and marginal contact occurs as Nembhard navigates over the pick.
Hield (IND) moves alongside Simons' (POR) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Hield (IND) legally contests Simons' (POR) jump shot attempt.
Nurkic (POR) and Turner (IND) mutually engage and disengage during the rebound and the contact is marginal.
Hart (POR) makes last contact with the ball prior to it going out of bounds. Possession is properly conferred to Indiana.
Turner (IND) establishes himself in Grant's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the pick.
Grant (POR) legally contests Haliburton's (IND) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Hield (IND) legally contests Simons' (POR) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Nesmith (IND) and Grant (POR) mutually engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and marginal contact occurs.

Haliburton (IND) brings his arm towards the ball and marginal contact occurs with Hart's (POR) head during the rebounding opportunity. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Nurkic (POR) jumps from point A to point B and initiates contact with Nesmith (IND), which affects his driving shot attempt.
Nembhard (IND) moves alongside Lillard's (POR) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
The shot clock expires with Haliburton (IND) in possession of the ball. Possession is properly awarded to Portland.
